Phase 2: Instrumentation Layer — Building the Interaction Trace Φ
🎯 What Are We Building?
Phase 2 is the brain of the GUIDE system. We're building the Interaction Trace (Φ) — an append-only event log that silently captures everything the candidate does:

Every AI prompt and response (already partially done in Phase 1)
Every code change (diffs computed when the candidate edits code)
Every test run result (when the candidate clicks "Run Tests")
Session start and session end markers
IMPORTANT

Why Φ matters: In Phase 3, the Evaluation Engine will read Φ to produce the 5 pillar GUIDE scores. If Φ doesn't capture something, we can't evaluate it. Get this right and evaluation becomes straightforward.

📚 Concepts You'll Learn
Concept	Where Used
Append-only log	Events are never updated once written — ensures data integrity
Debouncing	Firing code save events at most every 3 seconds to avoid flooding
Unified diffs	Computing what changed between two code snapshots
Subprocess execution	Running test suites in a sandboxed child process
useEffect cleanup	Properly cleaning up intervals/listeners when components unmount
Event-driven architecture	Every action becomes a structured event in Φ
